{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2322fcc-9cf3-4c58-ae3c-70ad4376707c","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For Theory:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int x) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in results, and the reason string appears in test output/reports.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"65c926c6-f81b-4317-b645-4e4691599c0b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":273,"requestId":"9818:37A270:1BA2FC:23E352:69FFDC0D"},"id":"01e6b972-704b-4464-8d95-78599a4aafcb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:14:59.324Z","parentId":"eec14e26-1721-4c70-b2a8-9b463f493bbe"}
